## 1. Canonical local\uc0\u8209 dev SOP (Cloud SQL via `gcloud`)\
\
You can drop this (or a variant) into your onboarding docs as \'93Local Dev \'96 Cloud SQL SOP\'94:\

\f1\b # Local Dev SOP \'96 Nexus Enterprise (Cloud SQL via gcloud)\
\
## One-time setup per machine\
\
1. Install tools\
   - Google Cloud SDK (gcloud + cloud-sql-proxy in PATH)\
   - Node + npm (matching project version)\
   - Docker Desktop (for other infra, even though Cloud SQL is remote)\
\
2. Authenticate to GCP for dev\
   # Log in for gcloud CLI and Application Default Credentials\
   gcloud auth login\
   gcloud auth application-default login\
   gcloud config set project nexus-enterprise-480610\
\
3. Set dev DB password in your shell profile (DO NOT commit this anywhere)\
   # In ~/.zshrc (example):\
   export DEV_DB_PASSWORD='your-dev-db-password'\
\
   # Then reload:\
   source ~/.zshrc\
\
## Daily dev workflow\
\
1. Open a terminal in the repo root:\
   cd ~/nexus-enterprise\
\
2. Make sure no stale proxies are running:\
   pkill -f cloud-sql-proxy || true\
\
3. Start the full dev stack:\
   ./start-dev.sh\
\
   This will:\
   - Kill anything on ports 3000, 8000, 5432, 6380\
   - Stop local Docker infra (if running)\
   - Start Cloud SQL Auth Proxy to nexusdev-v2 on 127.0.0.1:5434 using your gcloud ADC\
   - Start API dev server on http://localhost:8000\
   - Start API worker (BullMQ, imports)\
   - Start web dev server on http://localhost:3000\
\
4. Troubleshooting\
   - Cloud SQL proxy issues: check logs/cloud-sql-proxy.log\
   - API issues: check logs/api-dev.log\
   - Web issues: check logs/web-dev.log
